						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in the south <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Chōḷēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This inscription in Tamil characters of about the 12<hi rend="italic">th</hi> century records that the flight of steps <hi rend="italic">(sōpāna)</hi> and the cloister round the shrine <hi rend="italic">(tirunaḍai-māḷigai)</hi> were built by Nilaimaiyaḻagiyāṉ. Below the last line of the inscription is a sketch of a <hi rend="italic">kumbha</hi> flanked by lamp-stand ?</p>						

						<p>Cf. Inscriptions (Texts) of the Pudukkottai State, No. 1009.</p>						

						</summary>
